Text: Hi Teacher2.
I'm very sorry about the late blog post.
I have been focused over the weekend until now on a project milestone for info202 and I got stuck on trying to figure out something in Java and completely forgot to write it.
The week has been very productive though.
The sprint for me was pretty much perfect time predictions for my total task.

I may have spent 3-4 hours longer than our planning poker predicted (i didnt really count) but it felt pretty close to about 15 hours total to go from nothing to a working API call with all the required parameters and a parsed string to pass on the rabbitMQ.
However we anticipated having to create an OAuth client in the planning but i was able to get a permissioned access token with the particle CLI.
I still spent several hours researching to figure that out though.

I changed to using the node-fetch API module after some further reading which was very intuitive and let me write a loop and if statement for the offline objects and their last online time and wrap it all in a configurable poll function as per the brief.
Here the code, i left out some characters of the access token incase someone else reads this blog but it does work.
We met as a team this morning to go over it and catchup on how its going to like with the queue and nodemailer.
Gogo said rabbitMQ will take a string variable so he is working on that and Kiki is still getting nodemailer set up.
I ma not sure whether it is a good idea to upload the code containing the access token to github, i have read not too so to be on the safe side i haven't.
As for upcoming challenges i see that getting the whole system working might be a bit tricky but hopefully we can work though it and have to by the end of this week.
I have looked at nodemailer and it looks interesting so i will learn more about that tomorrow.
Also finally i was going to mention i have to go to the dentist on friday at 2pm for an urgent treatment.
This was the closest available time they had but I may be able to rebook it if there is something important coming up on Friday though.
Cheers Toto
Overall
